<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871104-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Group Increases StakeIn Trans-Lux to 7.97%</HL><DD> 11/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TLXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   A group including Cenith Partners L.P. said it raised its stake in Trans-Lux Corp. to 7.97% of the common shares outstanding.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the group said it holds 121,518 Trans-Lux common shares, including 27,100 shares purchased from Oct. 15 to last Friday for $8.043 to $11.123 a share. The group didn't say why it increased its holdings in Trans-Lux, which is based in Norwalk, Conn.    A spokesman for Boston-based Cenith Partners wasn't available for further comment. </TEXT></DOC>